==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bumboat
<hw>Bum"boat`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>bum</ets> the buttocks, on account of its clumsy form; or fr. D.
<ets>bun</ets> a box for holding fish in a boat.]</ety>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A clumsy boat, used for conveying provisions,
fruit, etc., for sale, to vessels lying in port or off shore.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bumkin</ent>⟦br⟧
